<TITLE> Poet Ikhtisad Ahmed unveils 'Cryptic Verses' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 11 (bdnews24.com)A new book of English poetry by Ikhtisad Ahmed titled 'Cryptic Verses' was launched at the National Press Club Friday. Ikhtisad's new work takes classical Greek mythology and romance as its inspiration. The author is the grandson of the late language movement veteran and poet Mahbub ul Alam Chowdhury and works as a lawyer in London. Ikhtisad also helped establish human-rights based NGO Shimanto in 2009, which works in the fields of law and education. Cryptic Verses marks the author's first sortie into the world of poetry, although he has previously had a number of legal articles published in different journals. The book was introduced by Prof Kabir Chowdhu
